eCPM. That's $1 for every thousand ad impressions.

00:12:22.120 --> 00:12:31.440
They are offering you 83% fill rate. So your
expected revenue per thousand requests is

00:12:31.440 --> 00:12:36.800
going to be a dollar multiplied by 83%, or
83 cents. So for every ad request, you are

00:12:36.800 --> 00:12:42.840
going to make 83 cents.
Now, ad network B is offering you a $3 eCPM,

00:12:42.840 --> 00:12:48.990
which is $2 more than network A, yet they
only fill 25% of their ad requests. So for

00:12:48.990 --> 00:12:54.650
every hundred ad requests, you only get 25
ads.

00:12:54.650 --> 00:13:04.360
So $3 eCPM multiplied by 25% fill rate, 75
cents. So you can see eCPM of network B is

00:13:04.360 --> 00:13:08.470
much larger than network A but you will be
make being more money, your revenue will be

